For your `img`, you&#39;ll pry want the width of that to be a %, so it will adjust for different screen sizes. You only need to give the `img` a width, the height will be created automatically based on the aspect ratio of the image. I would also set a `max-width` to control the image from not taking over the screen on bigger screens.  Try the below code for your `img`:

    img {
      width: 50%;
      max-width: 400px;
      margin-left: 80px;
    }

