Reduce is a very handy array method specifically for accumulating results when iterating over a collection.

Reduce takes a function as an argument, the function generally uses two arguments: the accumulator and the current element. The second argument given to reduce is the initial accumulator. I&#39;ve defined the two result arrays which allows me to push to them for every iteration.

